        pos.append([x, y, 0.0])
mic_positions = np.array(pos).T  # shape (3, 16)
```

**Angular resolution** with this small aperture is poor at drone-relevant frequencies. At **1 kHz** the beamwidth exceeds 150°; at **4 kHz** it narrows to roughly **45–50°** with conventional beamforming. Meaningful spatial resolution only emerges above **2 kHz**, and super-resolution methods (MUSIC) can improve this to ~15° at 2 kHz under good SNR conditions.

### Calibration and quirks

No per-unit calibration files ship with the UMA-16V2. The SPH1668LM4H-1 microphones have ±1 dB sensitivity tolerance, meaning up to 2 dB spread across the 16 channels. For precision beamforming, **record a known reference source and compute per-channel gain/phase corrections**. On Windows, the standard WDM driver does not support 16 channels — ASIO is required. Linux and macOS work driverlessly.

